_sText:
Good Evening,

I have completed making a new cs_crackhouse map for the HG and F5 community. I have spent about four days on the map so may need some touching up but it should be pretty well ready to go. The map was completely remade from scratch so there will be differences in heights, wall thickness (Prevent feet from showing through) and much more. I have tested it inside and out seems to be working pretty smooth. There are no buy zones, hostage rescue or bomb sites. I kept those all off as it is more of a DM map. Also there are quite a few screenshots but I wanted to allow you to view before downloading.

Map Objective

The sole purpose of this map was to make it so the map is not one sided. If you have great players on a single team they will eventually destroy the opponents to the point you can't even leave spawn. I also wanted to make a few differences to allow some what of a change to the map. Adding in a few extra spots and changing already existing areas. Also of course I wanted to make it FUN!

I am open to critique and ideas. So if you play it and think something may be better please do not hesitate to ask and or point it out! All in all I hope to see this map on the cs_crackhouse server in the future and I hope all the players enjoy it as much as I enjoyed making it! I also do not know the original author of cs_crackhouse but shout out to them as I my map is based on it.

Hello all, this is my first upload on here since about a year ago. This map is a regular CS:S deathmatch course. It is symetrical for t's and ct's so there is no real advantage for either... at the center of the course is the mausoleum, there are two doors, one for each team, hit "use" to open the door. A flashlight is recommended for inside the laberynth style mausoleum, as it is entirely dark, adding to the experience of the course. A flashlight is not required for the outdoors however. The outdoors consists of the two starting graveyards, and the two paths around the mausoleum. One side is an extended graveyard. Tombstones and rocks may provide cover. the other side is a spooky forest. both sides are divided by a river, one side has a bridge, but the other does not. Fun for teams of all sizes, please Download and tell me what you think! :)

/////Important info: This map is made up in a way that there are no multiple spawns in any single round. And there are no buys zones at all. All weapons, i,e; shot gun, sniper, Ak-47, Mp5 are all in the middle of each open area or corner of the map. You will spawn with the default hand gun and knife. You must incapacitate apposing team mates before they reach the cache's or just grab the heavier weapons first and then incapacitate them. Each spawn zone is made up of one(1) CT and one(1) T spawn and all are out of the line of sight and fire of the opposing team mates. These weapon caches are in between every set of CT and T spawn zones. There are four(4) guns in every area, three(3) rifles and one(1) degal or Elite. Also the Scout and saw m249 are in the middle of the map between the stacks of containers. There are various elites, frags and smoke grenades scattered around the map as well.///// 


Counter Strike: Source SDK map readme
What: SDK level TDM_Shipment
Why: It is a CODMW MP map remake
-------------------------------------------------------------
CONTENTS:
1.What is in the folders
2.Description
3.Know issues and notes
4.Why I made this map
-------------------------------------------------------------

1. Whats In The Folders:

1xReadme.txt file
1xtdm_shipment.vmf file
1xtdm_shipment.nav file
-------------------------------------------------------------

2.Description:

This is a remake(an entirely rebuilt version)of the map called Shipment that was made for Call of Duty: Modern Warfare that I made using the Source SDK from VALVE. I really liked the CODMW map and thought it would be fun not only to play in CSS but also to better my skills in VALVE's Source SDK. My remake is slightly different mostly being that I added a closer crane and a few more trees(I think)and obviously the map is sized and textured different but for the most part it resembles the main idea of what the original map looks like. Though nothing will ever replace the original.
--------------------------------------------------------------

3.Known Issues:

First off the map is NOT done I'm just trying to get feed back from any body who likes to give others feed back.

Its also not tailored to be used on line yet.

It has lighting issues, as I am not as good in the SDK as I wish I was(yet!)

Some of the props are out of place. And a few other set pieces need to be adjusted.

Textures are not 100% fitted to there brushes yet ether!

Um...Oh! There is no water 0.o! Some times when I work in the editor for to long or some times after I've added to much stuff, any water no matter dx7 or above, nor cheap water or nice water will render after this odd problem first occurs. Not sure why yet but I'm gonna try and figure it out.

That is about it I suppose, hopefully you be letting me know whats up/wrong from this point on=)
--------------------------------------------------------------

4. Why I Made This Map:

Not much to say that isn't already known about why any body would wanna remake this map...ITS BECAUSE ITS AWESOME! I've seen a ton of remakes and remixes on youtube so I think the original map speaks for its self in the reasons why it deserves to be worshiped(not really I know I'm just kidding)

And that's it...

Thanx for taking the time to check out my map and I hope you ether have playing it or getting to rip/critic it.

As always,
Arrogant Orange
